#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1632
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Dealing with Enemies</title>"
msgstr "<title>Håndtér fjender</title>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1636
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can always trap a single oncoming enemy in one hole, get his gold and "
"run on over him without killing him. It is often a good idea to dig behind "
"you and delay him further, but that might kill him. In some levels it is not "
"a good idea to kill enemies."
msgstr ""
"Du kan altid fange en enligt ankommende fjende i et hul, tage hans guld og "
"løbe over ham uden at dræbe ham. Det er ofte en god idé at grave bagved dig "
"og forsinke ham yderligere, men det kan måske dræbe ham. På visse niveauer "
"er det ikke en god idé at dræbe fjender."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1642
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "You can usually trap two oncoming enemies in two holes, get their gold "
#| "and run on over them, but this is dangerous if the enemies are separated "
#| "by two or three spaces. Sometimes two holes kill one of the enemies and "
#| "the other escapes and sometimes both escape."
msgid ""
"You can usually trap two oncoming enemies in two holes, get their gold and "
"run on over them, but this is dangerous if the enemies are separated by two "
"or three spaces. Sometimes two holes kill one of the enemies and the other "
"escapes and sometimes both escape. In &kgoldrunner; rules it is easier to "
"trap two enemies and run over them, because they stay in the holes for "
"longer."
msgstr ""
"Du kan oftest fange to ankommende fjender i to huller, tage deres guld og "
"løbe over dem, men det er farligt hvis fjenderne adskilles af to eller tre "
"mellemrum. Ind i  mellem dræber to huller en af fjenderne, og den anden "
"undslipper, og engang i mellem undslipper begge."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1650
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is nearly always impossible to trap three oncoming enemies and run on "
"over them. You will have to kill them, dig and drop through the floor or "
"simply run away."
msgstr ""
"Det er næste altid umuligt at fange tre ankommende fjender og løbe over dem. "
"Du skal dræbe dem, grave og hoppe ned gennem gulvet eller blot løbe din vej."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1655
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Try to get all the enemies running together in one group. That way you will "
"not get surrounded and you can do such fun things as collect gold while they "
"run along behind you."
msgstr ""
"Forsøg at få alle fjender til at løbe sammen i en gruppe. På den måde bliver "
"du ikke omringet og kan gøre morsomme ting, som at indsamle guld mens de "
"løber omkring bag dig."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1660
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sometimes you can kill an enemy with two holes, but it often takes three to "
"nine holes to kill one to five enemies."
msgstr ""
"Ind i mellem kan du dræbe en fjende med to huller, men ofte kræves der fra "
"tre op til ni huller for at dræbe en til fem fjender."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1664
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is possible to kill an enemy with one hole if he is far enough away when "
"you dig it."
msgstr ""
"Det er muligt at dræbe en fjende med et hul hvis han er langt nok borte når "
"du graver det."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1668
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <quote>Traditional</quote> game, you can trap an enemy permanently in "
"a pit of brick or concrete. Stand near the edge of the pit on the opposite "
"side to the enemy. As he approaches the pit, move down one square (to the "
"level of the floor of the pit) and the enemy will usually run into the pit."
msgstr ""
"Med <quote>traditionelle</quote> regler, kan du fange en fjende for evigt i "
"en grube af mursten eller beton. Stå nær grubens kant på modsatte side af "
"fjenden. Når han nærmer sig gruben, flyt et felt nedad (til niveauet for "
"grubens bund) så løber fjenden oftest ned i gruben."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1675
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In some levels in the <quote>Traditional</quote> game, you can force an "
"enemy to climb a ladder ahead of you if you stand somewhere above the bottom "
"of the ladder."
msgstr ""
"På visse niveauer med <quote>traditionelle</quote> regler, kan du tvinge en "
"fjende til at klatre opad en stige foran dig hvis du står et sted over "
"stigens bund."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1680
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <quote>&kgoldrunner;</quote> game, you can trap an enemy in a pit by "
"getting him to fall from above you, then running sideways and digging out "
"before he reaches you."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1685
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <quote>&kgoldrunner;</quote> game, enemies cannot run through dug "
"bricks, so you can sometimes use them as a barrier or hiding place."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1693
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Digging Puzzles</title>"
msgstr "<title>Graveproblemer</title>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1697
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To dig through more than one layer of bricks, start by digging as many "
"bricks as there are layers, jump in, dig one brick less and so on."
msgstr ""
"For at grave dig gennem mere end et lag mursten, begynd med at grave lige så "
"mange huller som der er lag, hop ned, grav en mursten mindre, og så videre."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1702
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you dig next to a ladder or a succession of bars, you can dig down "
"through any number of layers and up to five or six bricks horizontally. Just "
"return to the ladder or bars after digging each layer, then move down one "
"square, run out and dig the next layer."
msgstr ""
"Hvis du graver nær en stige eller en følge af stænger, kan du grave ned så "
"mange lag det skal være, og op til fem eller seks mursten vandret. Gå kun "
"tilbage til stigen eller stængerne efter hvert lag er gravet, gå et felt "
"ned, spring ud og grav næste lag."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1709
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a digging puzzle looks impossible, consider that there might be some "
"false bricks in it. Maybe the bottom layer is false or maybe you can stand "
"in a false brick and dig next to it."
msgstr ""
"Hvis et graveproblem virker umuligt, tænk på at der kan være nogle falske "
"mursten i det. Måske er underste lag falsk eller du kan måske stå midt i en "
"falsk mursten og grave ved siden af den."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1714
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Think about the order in which you will collect the gold. If you pick the "
"right order, the digging might be easier."
msgstr ""
"Gennemtænk rækkefølgen som du vil indsamle guldet. Hvis du vælger den "
"rigtige rækkefølge, kan gravningen blive lettere."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1718
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Some levels require you to dig away a brick walll, run in, collect some "
#| "gold and run out again before the bricks close up and trap you."
msgid ""
"Some levels require you to dig away a brick wall, run in, collect some gold "
"and run out again before the bricks close up and trap you."
msgstr ""
"Visse niveauer kræver at du graver en murstensvæg væk, løber ind, samler "
"lidt guld og løber ud igen inden murstenene lukkes igen og fanger dig."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1723
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is possible to dig while falling through empty space, if you can get the "
"timing right. You do not need to have an enemy to ride upon. This is a bug "
"which has become a <quote>feature</quote> and is used extensively in the "
"<quote>State of Terror</quote>, <quote>Count</quote> and <quote>Curse of the "
"Mummy</quote> games."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1734
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Tricks with Gold</title>"
msgstr "<title>Trick med guld</title>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1738
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you cannot get to a piece of gold, think about getting an enemy to go "
"there and get it. Even think about using an enemy's head as a bridge to get "
"across a pit or precipice."
msgstr ""
"Hvis du ikke kan komme til en guldklump, så overvej at få en fjende at gå "
"derhen og hente den. Overvej til og med at bruge fjendens hovede som en bro "
"for at komme over en grube eller sænkning."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1743
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In some levels there is a nugget that must be collected last of all, because "
"you will need the hidden ladders to get away from that position."
msgstr ""
"På visse niveauer er der en guldklump som skal hentes til allersidst, "
"eftersom du vil behøve de skjulte stiger for at komme fra dets position."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1748
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In some situations an enemy can be killed without giving up the gold he is "
"carrying. The gold becomes a <quote>lost nugget</quote>. You score no points "
"for making an enemy lose a nugget, but at least you can finish the level."
msgstr ""
"I visse tilfælde kan en fjende dræbes uden at han opgiver guldet som han "
"bærer på. Guldet bliver til en <quote>tabt guldklump</quote>. Du får ingen "
"points for at fjenden tabte sit guld, men du kan i det mindste afslutte "
"niveauet."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1754
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If there is nowhere to dig, keep the enemies running over concrete and the "
"tops of ladders and so make them release their gold at random."
msgstr ""
"Hvis der ikke findes noget sted at grave, så lad fjenderne løbe over betonen "
"og længst op på stigerne, for på den måde få dem at efterlade deres guld på "
"tilfældige steder."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1763
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Solving Difficult Levels</title>"
msgstr "<title>Løsning af svære niveauer</title>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1767
#, no-c-format
msgid "Try changing the speed settings to Beginner or even lower."
msgstr ""
"Forsøg at ændre hastighedsindstillingerne til nybegyndere eller til og med "
"endnu lavere."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1770
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the Editor feature to <quote>peek</quote> at where the false bricks and "
"hidden ladders are."
msgstr ""
"Brug editorfunktionen for at <quote>kigge</quote> hvor falske mursten og "
"gemte stiger findes."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1774
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the Editor feature to save the level in one of your own games, then you "
"can edit it so that you do not always have to start at the beginning when "
"you die. This allows you to develop the solution in easier stages."
msgstr ""
"Brug editorfunktionen til at gemme niveauet i et af dine egne spil. Derefter "
"kan du redigere det så du ikke altid skal starte fra begyndelsen når du dør. "
"Det lader dig udvikle løsningen i enklere trin."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1780
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In digging puzzles, look for false bricks you can fall into and thus have "
"one less brick to dig. Or consider using an enemy to go ahead of you, so "
"that you can stand on his head and dig."
msgstr ""
"Ved graveproblemer, led efter falske mursten du kan falde ned i og således "
"have en mursten mindre at grave. Eller overvej at bruge en fjende som går "
"foran dig, så at du kan stå på hans hovede og grave."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1785
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Look for a theme or trick in the level, such as riding down on an enemy's "
"head, trapping all the enemies in a pit, luring the enemies to a corner "
"where they will stay and not chase you, luring the enemies into pits you "
"must cross to get to some gold, getting the enemies to fetch gold for you or "
"finding spots where you can stand and make an enemy move to where you want "
"him."
msgstr ""
"Led efter et tema eller trick på niveauet, såsom at ride ned på en fjendes "
"hoved, fange alle fjender i en grube, lure fjenderne ind i et hjørne hvor de "
"står og ikke længere jager dig, lure fjenderne ind i gruber du skal krydse "
"for at komme til en del guld, få fjenderne til at hente guld til dig, eller "
"find steder hvor du kan stå for at få en fjende at gå derhen hvor du vil "
"have ham."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1793
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the <menuchoice><guimenu>Move</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Show a Solution</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item to check if there is a recorded solution "
"to the level. This will show you some ways to handle difficulties in the "
"level, but not necessarily the best ways. There are often many ways to win a "
"level and each time you play it there are small differences in timing, &etc; "
"So you probably will not be able to copy the recorded solution exactly."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1802
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use <menuchoice><guimenu>Move</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Instant Replay</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> or <menuchoice><guimenu>Move</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Replay Last Level</guimenuitem></menuchoice> to replay a level "
"to a point just before you had trouble, then interrupt the replay and try "
"some other approach."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1834
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Credits and Licenses"
